While researching cybercrime, I was surprised to learn how easily people fall victim to UPI fraud due to lack of awareness. Many scams rely on simple tricks such as creating urgency or pretending to be a trusted authority. I realized that even basic mistakes, like approving unknown payment requests or sharing OTPs, can lead to serious financial loss.

This task helped me understand the importance of being cautious while using digital payment platforms. One habit I will change is carefully verifying every payment request before approving it and never sharing sensitive information with anyone. Overall, this task increased my awareness of online threats and the steps needed to stay safe in the digital world.
